	<text_base_description>Once-in-a-lifetime opportunity to own the apex of The Hollywood Riviera, one of West Hollywood's most iconic and architecturally significant condo properties. This stunning 1954 mid-century masterpiece was designed by renowned architect Edward Fickett and has been featured in many TV shows, movies, and commercials. Arguably the best unit in the building, #39 is located at the front corner and with only 1 common wall, no one above or below, and easy access from front stairwell. Once inside, residents are greeted with an expansive living area w/ floor to ceiling windows looking out to lush tropical landscaping. The stylish staircase takes you to the upper floor which features soaring dramatic ceilings, a light filled bonus area w/ city views (perfect for home office), 2 spacious bedrooms and an updated bathroom. This condo also has central AC, 2 additional storage areas, 2 parking spots, low HOA dues including EQ insurance, and building is Mills Act approved </text_base_description>
